newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia 91-day Treasury bills yield 6.541 pct.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia 91-day Treasury bills yield 6.541 pct.

text.p: Malaysia's central bank said on Wednesday it accepted bids at an average yield of 6.541 percent at its auction of 91-day Treasury bills for 150 million ringgit.
At its previous auction on August 14 for 100 million, the central bank accepted bids at an average yield of 6.547 percent.
The bids accepted were in a high/low range of 6.550/500 percent against 6.550/538 a week ago, the central bank said.
Bank Negara will hold its next auction of 91-day Treasury bills on August 29 for 100 million ringgit.
